reviewText: My granddaughter loves to watch it.  She is three and watches as much as her mother will let her watch it and we will also watch it with her.
My 3 year old son loves this, I have seen it over and over. Good story line and more interesting than other Bob the Builders.
Nice family friendly movie with fun characters like Bob, the boys love all the trucks, tractors and building demolishing stuff going on
Another of Bob's adventures full of action. Workmanship, friendship, and even sportsmanship. My 5-yr old has watched again and again. Absolutely worth of keeping!

My three year old just discovered Bob about 2 months ago and he quickly supplanted Thomas and Little Einsteins as the most requested videos.  Gripper and Grabber are all the rage now.  Funny thing is that he seems to be enjoying the Rory the Racecar cartoon (one of the extras) more and more each day.  Watch out Bob, it a race to the finish!
Race to the Finish is my 4 year old's favorite DVD.  Gribber and Grabber are introduced in this DVD.
Our four year old grandson loved it. He watched it 3 or 4 times in a one week visit.
My kids love this Show. They watch it almost everyday.
Excellent.  5 yr old loves Bob the Builder

Well, it is a little hard to review since it was my 4 year old grandson who watched this.  But it held his attention until the end.  He loves Bob The Builder and this one was new to him.

Just as good as all the other videos in the series. Cute, likable characters appeal to both preschoolers and elementary aged children.

Bob the Builder holds my 3 year old grandson's interest and is one of his "go to" shows when choosing what to watch.  Keep in mind that the little guy loves trucks in all shapes and sizes so it's no surprise that he chooses this. Would recommend this series, especially for little boys.
Gret show for the little ones to watch.  It teaches great values for little ones to u dear stand at their level.
